Monday Bar Newsletter week 22 In this newsletter: MONDAY BAR CRUISE No 60 JUBILEE, 6-8 OCTOBER, 2023 • 2 night cruise to Tallinn, Estonia • Friday-Sunday, 41 hrs • Cabin bookings now online • Lineup presented.. 25 djs so far MONDAY BAR BLACK & WHITE CRUISE, MAY 17-19 • 344 amazing pictures by Timo Torvikoski Dear Monday Bar family, The Black & White cruise was just amazing. A 99% full ship with 50 djs and 2000+ happy ravers aging from 18-71 according to the passengers list. We've just put up 344 pictures by Timo Torvikoski. Have a look below and tag all your friends. Now we’re focusing on our next event, Monday Bar Cruise No 60 Jubilee, which will take place on the same ship, M/S Baltic Queen, Fri-Sun October 6-8. We're now in the process of booking djs but you can have a look at who we have booked so far on out Facebook event page and our Monday Bar homepage (see links below). Booking of cabins have just opened and and Tallink-Silja have asked us to remind all not to wait too long to book your preferred cabin type while they’re still available. Monday Bar crew 🥰 Who would have guessed over 20 years ago that we would sail together for the 60th time on the Baltic sea! We’ll, here we are, and it’s time again to board the best party ship of the Tallink-Silja fleet, M/S Baltic Queen. The cruise is in the beginning of October, but thanks to an outside sun deck partly covered with a roof and wind shield we should be able to enjoy a daytime party on deck while in port in Tallinn on Saturday. MONDAY BAR CRUISE No 60 JUBILEE Friday-Sunday October 6-8, 2023 (2 nights - 41h) M/S Baltic Queen Stockholm-Tallinn-Stockholm Cruise times Departure, Stockholm Tallink-Silja ferry terminal, Värtahamnen Friday, October 6, 17:30 (5:30 PM), local Swedish time Arrival, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 10:45 (10:45 AM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Departure, Tallinn Tallink D-terminal Saturday October 7, 18:00 (6 PM), local Estonian time (+1 hour) Arrival, Stockholm Tallink-